{"word":"H1497 - גָּזַל - gâzal - gaw-zal' - Catch","slug":"H1497","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">גָּזַל</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>gâzal"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>gaw-zal'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Catch"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D2;&#x05BC;&#x05D6;&#x05DC; - ga&#x0302;zal</b> - <i>gaw-zal'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>pluck</i> off; specifically to <i>flay</i>, <i>strip</i> or <i>rob: - </i>catch, consume, exercise [robbery], pluck (off), rob, spoil, take away (by force, violence), tear."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H1498\">H1498</a>, <a href=\"#/H1499\">H1499</a>, <a href=\"#/H1500\">H1500</a>"}]}